<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal">
<head metal:use-macro="master.macros['head']">
<metal:block fill-slot="headslot">

<title>Searching a patient</title>

</metal:block>
</head>

<body metal:use-macro="master.macros['master']">
<div id="content" metal:fill-slot="content">
Search form enter:
<ul><li>the patient identification number </li>
<li>or identification data, names, birthdate, sex.</li>
</ul>

<form id="patient_form" method="post" action="">
  <div tal:content="structure python:form.render()" />
  <div class="fa_field ui-widget">
    <input class="ui-button ui-state-default ui-corner-all"
           value="Search" type="submit" />
  </div>
</form>

<span class="error" tal:content="errors">error string</span>

<div tal:condition="python: number is not None">
<h4><span>There are ${number} results</span></h4>

<ul>
  <li tal:repeat="patient results">
    <a href="${patient.id}/list">${patient.id} : ${patient.name} ${patient.firstname}, ${patient.birthdate}, ${patient.sex}</a>
  </li>
</ul>
</div>

<div tal:condition="python: searched is not None">
If the right patient was not found <a href="add?${add_data}">Add a new patient record</a><br/>
If not sure, add a new record.
</div>

</div>
</body>
</html>
